result.execSummary:
The defendant Denzel M. Vaughn was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

01:49 PM   Attorney Rosa Delgado appeared for the State. Defendant, Denzel M. Vaughn, appeared in custody with Attorney Joseph Corcoran. Court Reporter:  Kimberly Keel. Clerk N. Nobile.
MINUTES:   Victim rights compliance. Agreement placed on the record by Attorney Corcoran. On State's motion the repeater enhancer is stricken from count 2. Defendant entered a plea of guilty to count 2; found guilty by the court. On State's motion count 1 is dismissed and read in. Parties request to waive the presentence investigation; Court grants request. Sentencing arguments heard. Defendant is sentenced to 9 months in the Kenosha County Jail with good time. Credit for 233 days. Court costs and DNA surcharge ordered, 60 days to pay or civil judgment. Defendant is ordered to submit a DNA sample; written notice provided to defendant in court. No restitution ordered. No prosecution costs ordered.  Appeal Rights given.
The 7/27/2022 Hearing has been rescheduled to 9/8/2022 at 1:45 pm due to a week long jury trial.
